u003C/orig>\n                    \u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\" n=\"20\">\u003Cdesc>[-?-]\u003C/desc>\u003C/gap>\n                    \u003Cw n=\"25\" lemma=\"XV\">XV\u003C/w>\n                    \u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\" n=\"30\">\u003Cdesc>[-?-]\u003C/desc>\u003C/gap>\n                \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\n                        \u003Cnote>Text of Gualtherus\u003C/note>\n                    \u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\">\n                \u003Cp>\u003C!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div-->\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\">\n                \u003Cp>Gualtherus presents the text as the preserved left margin with the second and third lines indented, and implying a space between EST and V in line 2. It would be possible to restore this as for a Ces[tius], with a form such as [hic situs] est v[ixit annos] XV..., for which there are parallels at Termini.\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Gualtherus\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1624\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>no. 112\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GIN6NANU\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002388\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                    \u003Cbibl>\n                        \u003Cauthor>Gualtherus\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Cdate>1624 [1625]\u003C/date>\n           